caption: Avoid brunch. Dinner has been consistently just ok, but not great... The plating also works against them and their choice of table size, so be prepared to balance things on the edges of the table if you order more than 2 plates. Brunch was pretty horrible; it's like they are afraid of salt.. The breakfast potatoes were very... "al dente" not in an enjoyable way and the eggs were very overcooked and rubbery.  I feel like a little quality control here would really turn things around because the menu is strong, just poorly executed.

I was sooo excited for this place. I really really wanted to like it. Cool location, cool vibes. Great mocktails tho. I may change my review if I go again, bc I only tired the risotto balls and the spaghetti, which both lacked flavor. An Italian restaurant, its the assumption that the actual Italian food, i.e., spaghetti, is better than anything you can get from anywhere. Like I said, I may go back and next time I hope whatever I order, it tastes better.
Everything we ordered was really good. Staff was kind and attentive.
Great service and delicious food
Super yummy place! My boyfriend and I ordered the beet salad, margherita pizza, mimosa, and small cheese board! We fully enjoyed everything. Definitely will be back again.

Being my first experience out in Chicago since restaurants have opened back up, I was not disappointed! The staff was friendly, attentive, and very helpful in accommodating a gluten allergy. Food was fast, fresh and comforting. Wine was superb! Atmosphere was modern and music was lively. Overall a great experience and will definitely be back.
It was great! Nice they are open during covid! The food and service was great
Good food and service.  Drinks were great.
Delicious food, great ambiance and great service!!! Loved it!!!
Great neighborhood Italian restaurant with solid cocktails. I could nitpick with the food I ate, but its better than anything you're going to be able to cook at home.
So good! They have the best gin and tonic. Definitely recommend!!

amazing. Such a cute little Italian place. Went here for Fathers Day and it was a perfect dinner before going to the Dodgers game. Not too bad of prices for some of the best pasta I've had. And I just went to Italy so that says a lot!! I loveeeee 10/10 recommend and will be back soon for sure !
I really loved their dishes and customer service, awesome area very close to my apartment. The employees are always nice. Will visit here again.
The food and staff are amazing, overall great relaxing atmosphere
The food and drinks were so good it's a must try.
Friendly and great staff
Good Pizza
Such a great place. Food was delicious. Great portion size. My favorite part was the blue berry French Toast, its was espectacular!!! Definitely will be going again.

Honestly, the brunch was pretty terrible. Bloody mary was flavorless and tasted like straight vodka. Breakfast potatoes were undercooked. Friendly staff though. And good COVID protocols. I'd try it again for dinner :)
Service is excellent food was excellent drinks or most impressive. I will be back again very soon.
We had some delicious Benedicts for brunch. Food was great, the outdoor seating was comfy and the staff was really good. You should come try it out!
The pizza is so good!
The food is always so delicious!
The mimosa, steak and 🥚 brunch was amazing!
The food was pretty decent but the service was slow and rather annoying. I'm not usually impatient but it felt quite unreasonable considering the place was really slow at the time of our visit.

Cioppino is an SF invention, and if you want to get a sense of SF history, then Sotto Mare's crab cioppino is a must try! This is why we picked Sotto Mare as #2 in our SF Must Eats video (check out our video on the YouTube channel two BIG bites). A lot of other cioppinos don't have crab inside, and they don't have ziti pasta either. The seafood inside is so plentiful and fresh and the broth is addicting. It's totally worth it and large enough for two!

SABA Italian Bar + Kitchen is a quality choice for pizza. They serve deep dish with a corn bread crust. Not as good as Chicago style, but certainly a satisfying pie. They also have really good gluten free crust, if you're into that. Unfortunately they aren't open for lunch, but give them a try for dinner!

I visit this place a lot since I work right next to it. I like how their customer service is always good and they keep the place well kept at all times. Rates are reasonable and they serve generous portions.
(Translated by Google) In spectacular bear.  (Original) In osobuco espectacular.
Excellent food and even better service!  The Cesar Salad and Mushroom Pizza rock!
Good brunch, takes reservations via open table

I had the worst experience at Saba on 2/29/2020. The food was cold,  the server Giselle seemed even colder.  I had to ask for everything,  and each time she approached our table with attitude. I  still tipped her, so hopeful she'll be nicer to the next customer.  Money wasted,  I won't be back.
Only had happy hour drinks here but very sleek place.  I like it!
Cod didn’t taste fresh. Salad was good.
We love the friendly service and atmosphere. Hands down the best food!
Great atmosphere. Great food. TERRIBLE service. Every time. The food is awesome but the service is consistently terrible and makes it not worth going. Do not bring friends here.
Saba has a welcoming staff with an exceptional food!!  Great for brunch or a romantic evening with your loved one.
Great happy hour. Kids eat free mon-wed and the  portion is huge. Great service.
Best carbonara I had for a lon time! Tiramisu is delicious! Good job ragazzi!!!

My husband and I visited Saba for the first time as part of restaurant week. We were excited to check out the restaurant as we live in the neighborhood. While the appetizers were delicious, I have to say the rest of the meal was just ok. The salads were boring (beet salad and iceberg with prosciutto/grapes). For the main course the pork chop was so overcooked it was a challenge to cut with the steak knife, and the seafood pasta was so spicy I could barely eat it. It seems like there was something going on in the kitchen because the wait between salad course and main course was very long, and perhaps the chop sat under a heater for too long (thus overcooked). Overall, the space is nice and the server was attentive. But I won’t make it a point to hurry back anytime soon.

Saba is one of my favorite spots in the neighborhood. Whether it's brunch or dinner, this place is quality every time. They have tons of offerings for different price ranges on one menu, which is great! They have an amazing week day happy hour deal that honestly can't be beat - and their drinks in general are always great. I am sad to hear that they are getting rid of their boozy Italian sodas, I hope they bring them back as specials in the summertime.
Nice local place great food.
Food was under cooked maybe drinks is there thing
Excellant service ok food

Eat in, take out, Saba nails it.  I'll start with the spaghetti & meatballs, since that's my fave thing on the menu so far.  It's phenomenal.  There is such depth of flavor n the meatballs- the sauce is perfect, and the pasta is al dente.  There is plenty of sauce, and the overall portion is hard to kill in one sitting.  My wife loves the chicken parm, which is 2 nice-sized, breaded and seared chicken breasts over that same excellent pasta– with lots of mozzarella, and tons of flavor.  We have both enjoyed the pizza, which is a flat-bread, Italian style.  And the brussels sprouts are also spot-on delicious.  The cauliflower is spiced on the very neutral side, so I would only order that again as a foil alongside a very spicy entree.  Prices are super reasonable, so I'm sure that Saba will endure and become a staple of our great neighborhood, Logan/Avondale!  :-D
Good desserts
Excellent service, food, and atmosphere. This place is chic, romantic gem. I've never been disappointed with their food or drinks. Try their beet salad, so refreshing!

Great service from the bartender. Loved the grilled caesar and steak tartare. Truffle pizza and veal ossabucco were delicious. Panna cotta was perfect. Great find. Restaurants on this street can blend in because there is so much to choose from. We will definitely be back to this one.

Came here with family and had an excellent experience. The dishes are thoughtful, delicious, and gorgeously plated. Everyone at the table enjoyed their dish. Will be returning to continue sampling the menu.
Rachel was so delightful, charming and professional. I enjoyed the food as much as Rachel.
A new spot. Very quite a quiet intimate setting good for lunch meetings. An awesome desserts!

I was disappointed with our meals. There was a bright point with the bruschetta, but our entrees were poorly executed. The osso bucco was overwhelmed by lemon that made it unpalatable. The ribeye special was unseasoned and tough. The papardelle was flavorless, unseasoned, and cold. Similarly the lobster ravioli was unappetizing. A glass of wine we ordered tasted like raisins, not a cabarnet. Management did try to rectify some issues by providing another entree and a complimentary dessert. The restaurant has interesting ideas, but the execution was very poor and I will not return.

What a cool spot!!  It is really hard to find a good Carbonara and let me tell you....... the carbonara was done to perfection!  I would have ordered another if the tiramisu wasn’t so delicious and filling...  Go here and combo the fried calamari, pasta carbonara, and the tiramisu. You will not be disappointed!  Upon walking in, Alyssa was a delight and we had no wait at all.  From entering the door, to the final bite of dessert, this place rocks!!
Nice ambiance and tasty brunch!
Gem in the neighborhood. Great ambiance. Customer service is superb. Friendly and attentive staff . Bruschetta with prosciutto was delicious. Pastas are delicious.. Definitely returning
I'm still dreaming of the seafood risotto. Pasta was excellent too. I can't wait to go back.  Wine and beer only.
The food was great, staff was attentive, and environment mellow. Overall a good experience.
I think this place is over price. I was not impressed with the food.
This place was amazing! The waiter was great and the owner was very sweet! The food was also amazing!
Love the pizza & clams.
One of my wifes favorite places to go. The food is really good and it a great vibe.
Love, love love this place. The food is absolutely amazing and service is great

Great options, attentive staff and really good ambience. Have seen people say prices are high but I actually found the entrees very fair. Owner was great and made sure all tables were doing ok. Would recommend 100%
It was fine.  Overall.  I could write paragraphs about like my experience, but honestly we all kept joking that everything was pretty much... fine.
Service was great. Omelette and potato's were a bit bland. But overall great experience.
Good vibe and location,  food was decent, but lacked the creativity I was expecting. Cocktails were great and price matches the ambiance they are trying to maintain.
We have had good experiences here on numerous Saturday night occasions, although service was really lacking here last Saturday night so hopefully it's not a longer term trend or deeper issue.

This was my favorite restaurant in the Avondale/Logan area until the recent* price hike and menu change. Food is still good, service is still good, but they no longer have the reasonably priced pasta options I grew to love.

Good Food, but not filling portions..I had the spaghetti and mearballs, then I went downtown and went to portillos less than an hour later as I was starving still..never had italian before where I was still hungry..would not probably eat here again

Have been going here since they have opened. I've never had a bad meal. While their prices have risen a bit, their quality has stayed on a high level. From their chicken, to fish to pork chops , spaghetti and meatballs and one of my favorites the cremini mushroom pizza ,they do not disappoint! Pet friendly in the summer outside. Enjoy the drinks and wine .They offer a happy hour also.

It had pretty good food.  It was pricey considering you do not get salad or bread with your meal.  Seems an Italian restaurant would have bread for sure.  My friend got ravioli and only got 7 stuffed raviolies (bite size).  Not filling.  It is a smaller place but has nice big windows.  We we're lucky to go when the window walls were open.

The menu and service were beyond my expectations. I really loved the vibes of this restaurant. First-rate place to take the family out for lunch.

Prices for the food are reasonable, however, their price for their wine is a bit much. You have to try their Gnocchi, it reminded us just how they serve it in Italy, Delicious!

Food was very good but service was abysmal. Staff was pleasant but never present. It was more than 2 hours after we arrived before we got our food. Over an hour before any one asked for our orders.  I would say it seemed rather disorganized over all.

Had a wonderful meal and entire night for our large party of 12. Octopus appetizer was delicious, as was the pesto gnocchi. Tiramisu was very good as well, but the best part of the evening was the service. Kyle, couldn't have been nicer. Made for a memorable evening!

Instead of going to Lula Cafe, our normal Logan date night spot, we decided to try Saba. The restaurant was full which was promising. Our server greeted and took an order from a table that sat down AFTER us, and we didn’t get greeted or served water until about 10 minutes after sitting. Our drinks took almost as long as the food, and our appetizer came out at the same time as the entrees. We ordered the Spanish octopus (which was almost impossible to cut through and over cooked), the half chicken (which was served with what seemed like old potatoes and a pile of bell peppers?), and a steak dish. I can’t understand how this restaurant is full in a neighborhood with so many great dining options. Would strongly recommend not spending money here.
Loved the appetizers. Pasta was mediocre
Simply okay

The food was delicious, with a broad menu, and the service was friendly. Very good watercress salad big enough to share, and delicious share-size mushroom pizza with a variety of cheeses and a bit of truffle oil. (For my taste, they could add a bit more of that oil!) Meatballs in the spaghetti -- tender and big -- were made of veal and seasoned just right. Beet salad was lovely, cooked perfectly, and generously portioned. Because all the food arrived at once when we were there, rather than staggered with salads first, the waiter offered a complimentary dessert to make up for the error. The only marginal element was the outdoor table and chairs. The metal chairs are not comfortable, and the tables don't fit together properly when placed side by side.

I've had to send back food multiple times because it was still half frozen, or otherwise just gross. Everything tastes frozen or pre-prepared and left to sit in the walk-in for hours. Service has also been hit or miss. I've had great bartenders and bartenders who ignored us all night, so who knows.  There's so much better food in this neighborhood, don't waste your money here.
This restaurant is alright. Nice space, the food is fine and the staff seems a little over worked. Over all it was an alright experience. Not bad but not great.
Had the mushroom risotto, it was creamy and full of flavor. Tiramisu was rich and decadent. It looked so good I forgot to take pictures, because I wanted to try it. Service was great.

My husband chose SABA for my birthday dinner. The service was fantastic. We tried the peroni with orange oil - loved it. The carpaccio, pesto gnocchi and filet mignon were all very good. Our server even surprised us with a birthday tiramisu which was one of the best I've had - maybe even better than the one I make.  Very pretty decor inside as well. Mille grazie per una buona sera!

Super awesome bartender!

My wife and I went to SABA last night, July 6, 2019, for our date night.  We agreed to drive to Logan Square and let the reviews and pictures be our guide.  We agreed on SABA.  We greated warmly and seated right away.  Our waiter came over right away.  This is where my review takes a turn.  After asking a few questuons about drinks we order drinks and then move over to the appetizers.  We attempted to order calamari and rizzuto balls. My wife said we would like the Calamari and Rizzuto balls. The waiter then simply said yes those are appetizers I said we know that us what we would like for right now.  The appetizers come and we are done before the waiter returns to take our main course order.  We order white fish and eggplant parm.  The food was ok.  Nothing for me to say I'll come back or I'll definitely tell my friends to try this spot.  So all that to say we paid for ho hum food, not so good service and a decent atmosphere. We aren't going back.
Had Beets salad and pizza. Great taste!
nice place, great pizza, frienly bartenders

Fantastic flavors. Surprising, if I'm honest. This is a pretty low-key spot to have this level of food and cocktails. The Carbonara and Cavatelli were so rich and delicious. Polpo is a must order. Will be back soon (after we run/ride/swim the calories off)!

First time here, Walked in greeted with a nicely. Easy to order, waiter was very helpful with veggie orders, and options. Went with a group I ordered spaghetti and meatballs and garlic mashed potatoes, drank water. A friend ordered meatballs and bread, another person ordered half chicken, And potatoes. It's all really good food. Love the atmosphere and service was good. Well recommend this place and try something new on the menu.

The food was okay, especially for the price. Honestly expected more out of my pasta. I’ve had better for cheaper, but some may think otherwise! Good to check out. Not my first recommendation in the neighborhood though.

This was the most average food I’ve ever had. Everything appeared to be good but when you take a bite you’re so underwhelmed. I would not eat here again but it seems the drinks are at least good. But what’s good drinks without good food? Had the calamari - wasn’t very crunchy and even the sauce wasn’t flavorful just very generic. Goat cheese was served with burned, hard toast (menu says focaccia). Had gnocchi with pesto - hard to mess up. They messed it up. Gnocchi was rubbery and dense and they poured on a gallon of pesto to cover it up. Normally wouldn’t complain about extra pesto except it was way way too salty. Technically it was grilled chicken gnocchi pesto but there was so little chicken they may as well left it off. Had a few other dishes as well but can barely remember them because they were so forgettable.  Even their own website as of 6/18/19 misspells prosciutto as prosiotto making you question if you’re even getting real meat.  Atmosphere: It’s supposed to be an Italian restaurant but they just decided to do generic modern American restaurant decor with random succulents hanging everywhere as I assume an attempt to fit into the neighborhood.  My prediction: this will either be a complete menu or concept overhaul or completely gone by next year. The only thing saving it is the location by the Logan Square blue line.  The only reason they got 2 stars instead of 1 is because it’s so hard to open a restaurant so I give them credit for just opening.  I saw in another review that they went through staff changes including the head chef. This may be why the older reviews are good.

Food was good, service was awful. There are too many good options nearby to consider going back. I'd suggest that everyone saves their money and goes somewhere else. It's a cool location, maybe a place where the servers aren't all super rude will move in.
Love the food and the atmosphere. I have gone here a handful of times and the service is always great.

The service and the food were great. My friend and I came here around lunch time on a Sunday so we got to try the brunch food as well as the pasta recommend by our server. The drinks were really good too, will definitely come back!

Came here with a few friends for a girls night, and was very pleased. The space was beautiful, the service was excellent, and the food and drinks were great!

The food is delicious and the waiters were very friendly. However, my family felt rushed and the prices are unreasonably high. They even charge you for bread, 1 Penney a slice, which I find ridiculous, never been to an Italian restaurant that doesn’t serve bread with the meal. They serve the water warm, which most people find lazy and unacceptable.

I'm absolutely delighted I finally decided to dine here this evening because the weather was perfect for people watching, the service was attentive and I truly enjoyed my order. Now let's go over what I ordered because now you're going to want to come here this week.  I picked two winners tonight; I chose a well prepared gnocchi which came with grilled chicken, grilled red peppers and fresh pine nuts and the Italian soda. I chose a non alcoholic version which was made with seltzer water, strawberry gelato and orange soda syrup.  It was decadent, refreshing and colorful. I absolutely loved my beautiful gnocchi but I wish there had been a non meat version.  When I perused the menu I didn't pay close attention to the ingredients listed so I hope this lovely restaurant can alter their menu in the future and offer a meatless version of gnocchi for a slightly lower price to accommodate vegetarian tastes too. I also noted they have very tempting salads but again the prices ate listed as $10 and over and I feel if you intend to order a dinner the restaurant should accommodate you with a half order of salad for half the price or as an add on option to your main course.  Bread is not included here but when I asked my server for bread he graciously made some crispy bread for me. I hope this wonderful establishment will consider offering a few slices of complementary bread to their diners who are ordering a main meal because bread isn't costly to make and everyone typically enjoys using bread to sop up remaining sauces in their pasta dish. I'll definitely repeat and I was very pleased altogether with my experience.  I hope the owner or manager will take my suggestions to heart.

I'm a retired airline piot.i have eaten in untold restaurants around the US and the world. This is the FIRST time that water was served with no ice. It had to be requested. Also the FIRST time that there was a charge for bread. Two of the ordered drinks weren't correct. The service was terrible, though the food was good. Don't think that I'll be back.
Lots of vegetarian options, if desired. Arancini was delicious. As was the fennel sausage rigatoni. Yummy to everything.

One of my favorite spots in the city. Drinks are excellent, and the food is great! I love their pizzas and pastas. The foccacia appetizer is really good too! The servers are all really fun and friendly. The atmosphere is really nice, not too casual but just fancy enough to feel special. They recently raised their food prices a bit, so this will become a special occasion place for us instead of being in our usual rotation. Highly recommend it!
EXCELLENT!! I WILL RETURN. GREAT FOOD & SERVICE.

My children brought me here for mothers day. The cocktails were really good and carried a punch. I tried vesper, loved it. We  loved salmon and white fish .braised short rib was ok.lobster ravioli was really good.tiramisu  and panna cota raspberry was yummy. over all we really enjoyed our time here. The service was phenomenal. The owner and the manager   came to our table. I recommend this place and would go back there.
What a great, versatile spot. I was welcomed late at night for a quick meal after work. I can see family dinners here, as well as the restaurant space appreciate for fancy business dinners.
No traditional Italian. Only trendy Italian.

The service was better than the food, we had ordered the Lobster Ravioli which my wife enjoyed but the Carbonara was definitely lacking flavor, again it could be me since I've eaten Italian in many parts of the world and the Canolis were ok at best.
Really great place to eat, food was great, and everyone here are friendly. 5 stars 👍

We love trying out new spots for Italian food and were thoroughly impressed with this place. The food was delicious, the service was great and it had a nice atmosphere. We will definitely return.
The food was sooo good and the desserts were high quality. Very great space as well.

My fiance and I arrived in Chicago hungry after a flight from Sacramento.  From Midway we took CTA to our destination.  That led us to the CTA Logan Square station at about 10pm. We were curious about SABA when walking the neighborhood in the past. At this time of the night we decided to try it since the other nearby options were a Mexican restaurant we weren't impressed with previously and a fast food restaurant that we wanted to avoid. We walked into SABA with our luggage, the restaurant was clearly emptying, but there were still people at the bar and tables. The host greeted us and, without our asking, he told us where to put the luggage safely out of the way. A waitress then promptly took our order, made some suggestions, and we sat down to brussel sprouts, a tomato and cheese side dish, pizza, and a bottle of wine. The food was delicious, but the wine didn't measure up to our California favorites (Russian River wines). Nonetheless, the rest of the meal was outstanding and we appreciated the considerate service.  We will be back and can recommend the restaurant.
Incredibly average Italian food
Amazing service

Great corner location, near Logan theatre. Sitting at the bar is grand and the staff is super friendly. The menu is a mixed experience. Small plates and pastas have quality ingredients and are fantastic but the pizzas are flat. THE DOUGH is a quick rise crust and comes out bland without chew or flavor. This seems like an easy fix - use a starter. I’ll go back but would consider Paulie Gees and Middlebrow for pizza.

Very rarely do I put up a poor review so I will keep this brief. This place used to be good and then it just stopped. All of the 5 star reviews are because of the old staff and head chef that were recently let go.  I'm not sure why the huge change of employees, from head chef, great bartenders and servers all gone!!!  From what I can tell, the owner appears extremely unagreeable. The couple of times I met him, I couldn't wait to leave his presence. I won't say don't go, but I will tell you I will not go back.

Went there for brunch today, had the meatballs appetizer they were delicious, the texture, the sauce they complemented each other perfectly, I also had the pasta perfect
Food and service were excellent.  Great atmosphere and the pappardelle is to die for!
Some of the best thin crust pizza in all of chicago.  Great cocktails too!
First time here with my girlfriend, great experience
Excellent food - especially love the brussel sprouts. Great drinks. Service is a little slow but by Logan Squat standards amazing.
Nice neighborhood spot with contemporary italian food. Love that they are open later as well
Always perfect
Clean, rustic, cool atmosphere. Great food that’s a more unique take on Italian fare. Staff has always been friendly! Love Saba! Happy hour specials are great, too.
Amazing food, nice atmosphere. It's not what you would expect and that's a good thing.

I was excited about this place, but the small plates weren’t my favorite. I so pretty unimpressed with the small plates, as they almost went down in taste from the first to the last. I didn’t get a chance to try any of the other items, so I’m excited to get back there and give their entrees a try... as that will really give me a good idea of how the restaurant is!

If I had a chance to try the food, this place could have earned a 3-4 star rating from me because the menu has a lot of seemingly tasty choices, the location is perfect, and the modern decor is beautiful. Unfortunately, in my TWO attempts to eat here in the last two weeks, I didn't get taste one bite.  Several weeks ago, they had the ENTIRE dining room booked for an event, and the only seats available were the bar or the tiny cocktail tables. We had a party of four, so neither was an option, and we had to choose some place else. At that point, it was what it was. Logan Square has so many great places to eat, we weren't going to cry because we weren't able to be accomodated that night.  When we finally got the chance to try this place for real several days later, enough had happened prior to ordering that we decided to get up and leave. First, we were seated for 15 minutes before a server came to bring us water or take drink orders. I've worked serving tables before, so I started paying attention to what was taking so long, and it turned out that she was in the weeds: she was the only server in the entire place and had every table (which almost all were full). Once she finally did get to us and we order drinks, she brought us practically clear cokes. The taste matched the color (weak), so I mentioned to her that they may need to change the syrup in the machine, to which she replied "but that is going to take me like 10 minutes because it is all the way downstairs." I told her that was fine, and I would appreciate that she tried because that is the drink I wanted. She came back about 1 minute later and said that "its just our coke. We get weird complaints about it all of the time, and I think it is just ours." I laughed inside. Are you kidding? I mean, really, kidding? Whatever. I'll drink the watered down coke, thanks for "trying" because you and I both know that you didn't even check. So now we are ready to order, and I should have known better to let the abnormal wait times, the watered down coke, and the poor service be a precursor: she announces that they are out of essential menu items that accounted for half of our table's meals LOLOL. No words. We left, and I won't be making a third attempt.
The meatballs and pizza were phenomenal. Great service and atmosphere! Not a fan of the Cesar salad. This place is a win.
Good prices, the chicken parmesan is delicious!
Great staff, good prices and great food!

I'm very skeptical when I see someone review a restaurant saying they had a bad experience. This is the first restaurant I've eaten at in Logan Square and my experience was very nice. I was greeted with a smile by two bartenders Barbara and Jess. They were great. I came by at 330 before dinner was served but the cod aranchini was light appetizer and pretty filling about 3-4oz balls. I had their bar burger and it was very good. Even though I'm just visiting chicago for food adventures I would gladly come back to try their dinner menu. Just based on the happy hour menu alone I was left satisfied and happy. Thank you Saba best of luck

I've been here twice now and really enjoy the atmosphere and food, and the prices are good as well. The chicken parmesan is fantastic!  Unfortunately, the service is pretty poor and way too slow. Both times I've been here, the server has apologized to us about how slow some of our meals were coming out. I was hoping the first time was a fluke, but have had the same experience both times coming here.
Had the chicken parmesan and it was delicious...it also seemed pretty reasonably priced
Super loud, out of half the pastas on the menu, really slow service.

Don’t let your 👀 deceive you, looks like it’s a high quality restaurant from the outside. Inside service is below average and ruins the entire experience. Food is tasty and unique however two out of the 4 pastas they debut on menu, were 86/out.  This is the 2nd time we have been here and each time, they are severely poorly understaffed and the service is beyond horrible. 40 min to get someone, anyone (which eventually became the hostess) to get to the table to refill drinks or take our lunch order. @ the time we sat down, there were only 2 other tables!  Mgmt needs help. Not one employee or mgr approached us to apologize for the poor service. Unfortunately, don’t think this restaurant will make it and will be closed in a month.
Delicious!

Great food. Service was very good. The waiter knew all about the restaurant background and the owner. He owns several on the block and it's revitalizing the neighborhood. There was a wait when we walked in Friday night at dinner. They out our phone number into the iPad and texted us way faster than their estimate, which never happens anywhere!

Saba had a really great menu. We started with the burrata and beets as an app. I've never been a big fan of beets but they pair so well with burrata. Next we had the cotechino which was paired with cannellini beans. Again, an interesting pairing that worked well. For main courses we the tagliatelle which came with an amazing pork and beef ragout. Easily my favorite dish. For the second entree we had the chicken parmesan.  Instead of being served on top of angel hair or another pasta it was served on a bed of polenta. I was not a fan of the polenta, it just made me think of grits too much.
Cute place. Drinks were a little sweet. Too much oil in the food.

Nice addition to LS, the service is good. We ordered the focaccia bread was great with the peppers and olive oil I liked it alot. The pizza was too bottom burned for me that the ingredients didn't shine through. The space is beautiful love all the touches throughout. They don't do anything special for birthdays
Delicious!

House made pasta. Fresh ingredients. Delightful flavor combinations. Excellent service. Perfect prices. Moderate portion sizes. Accommodating of allergey/dietary restrictions. The food reminded me of Italy--and that's the whole point, right? I would recommend the Ravioli if you like sweet savory combos. The Cavetelli was also delicious, as was the lamb pizza.  Do yourself a favor and check it out!
Love this place. Delicious and reasonable. Please keep this place open,go there and find out for yourself
Almost perfect!

This place was excellent. Fantastic food and the decor is really well done. It's spacious, so you don't feel like you're eating right on top of other people. The pasta is some of the best in the city, and the pizzas were also really great. Highly recommend you go check it out.
Food, drinks & service were great, but unfortunately  after eating their farro pasta with mushr [ms I had diarrhoea -reason for the  2 stars.
Great atmosphere, service and food. This is the gem that the neighborhood needed for awhile.
Great service, great food. Relaxed yet great quality
Stop reading reviews and just go. Damn fine

Great wine list, absolutely amazing food. We chose a number of things to share for the table, so we could taste as much as possible. The arancini was fantastic, & we were very happy with our sever's recommendations for pasta dishes. The pork chop was also perfect. The dessert/amaro list was also killer. The only dish we were not over-the-moon about was the crudo appetizer. It was just bland & not inticing. Service was great, attentive but not overbearing. Thanks for a great experience!

Another fantastic bar/restaurant added to the logan square neighborhood. If you are looking for chill ambiance, great food and even better drinks, look no further. Started with the meatballs (awesome) and the ravioli has an amazing light brown butter sauce.  10/10
Great food and drinks.  Get the meatballs and try all the pizzas.  Finish the meal with a shot of amoro
Pastas were fantastic. Pizza awsome, and service with a smile n very accommodating. I recommend. Absolutely.Alex was great...!

Wow. This place is tasty.  I got ravioli with parsnips, hazelnut and a brown butter sauce. The homemade pasta and the overall taste of the dish was so fresh, yet powerful.  My husband got an egg pasta with ragout sauce and it was scrumptious. I usually steer away from meat dishes, but this was incredible.  For dessert we got a panna cotta with a chocolate pudding, that was light and scrumptious.  Service was speedy and attentive.

I had a truly remarkable  meal last night at Saba! Thoughtful interior including outdoor space. The staff were extremely knowledgeable about the menu and offered great tips on food courses. The cocktail offering was simply outstanding - we worked with Genna who knew the best drink options as well as the menu backwards and forward. I cannot wait to go back and try more of the incredible menu. If you’re looking for a new spin on Italian cooking, Saba is the place. BRAVO!
They use the highest quality ingredients possible!!! Fresh and authentic!

Great service from Christine, our bartender! She had amazing recommendations for cocktails and food. Lovely atmosphere, outdoor area, open windows to bring in that breeze , and awesome music! Can’t wait to go back!
LOVED this place. Great atmosphere, good service, and the food was phenomenal! Will definitely be back.

Nothing but great things to say about this place. Fantastic Italian soda floats, salt cod arancini, hand tossed pizza, homemade pasta, panna cotta! All at a perfect price. Cannot wait to return with more friends!
They deliver in every single category. What a welcome addition to the neighborhood.

Honestly, I was very impressed with this place. I went just about the day they opened, and they already had their act together.  The food was great, but the drinks were the absolute highlight of the evening. I had 3 different cocktails, all of which were very well balanced and unique, and one cream soda. I left very happy with my experience.  I'm not sure if the lamb pizza is still on the menu, but it was fantastic.

My son took me for my birthday and it was by far the best experience I have had. The service is incredible. Very knowledgeable staff answered all my questions about the food and drink menu. Mark, the head chef came out and introduced himself and told us a little about the pasta special with lamb. We ordered that and the mushroom pizza. So delicious! Do yourself a favor and try out this place.
New Logan Square Italian restaurant & bar with exceptional food, drinks, atmosphere and service.

I've been here a few times and I still haven't had anything that wasnt incredible. The meatballs app and the brussel sprouts app are essential. If your have room, grab a pizza. You won't be disappointed.
Exciting nite at the new ⚘Saba⚘ Italian restaurant in Logan square  Congratulations it's absolutely beautiful and the food and service was famimol !!!
